# Global Rules

## Mission
Ship incremental, validated slices with explicit evidence and rollback notes.

## Core Workflow
1. Scope lock before editing.
2. Security gate before implementation.
3. Discovery first, then phased plan.
4. Execute one logical slice at a time.
5. Validate with syntax/build/tests/smoke.
6. Capture evidence and rollback command in handoff.

## Golden Rules
- Context is precious: reset between plan and execute phases.
- Commandify repetitive workflows.
- Prefer declarative config over runtime scripting when feasible.
- Do not finalize work without validation evidence.

## Tooling Contract
- Start non-trivial tasks with:
  - POST /workflow/plan
  - POST /workflow/run/start (with intent_contract)
  - GET /hints
- Keep tool/discovery outputs in project docs under .agent/workflows.
